# Neighbour Cell Scanner Implementation Tasks

## Phase 1: Backend Implementation
- [ ] Create `/usr/bin/qmanager_neighbour_scanner`
  - Implements singleton [(PID_FILE)](file:///d:/Projects/QM%20PROJECT/QManager/scripts/usr/bin/qmanager_cell_scanner#36-39) logic.
  - Queries `AT+QENG="neighbourcell"` for LTE neighbours.
  - Queries `AT+QNWCFG="nr5g_meas_info", 1` and `AT+QNWCFG="nr5g_meas_info"` for 5G neighbours.
  - Parses raw output into TSV format.
  - Uses `jq` to assemble the final `/tmp/qmanager_neighbour_scan_result.json` array.
- [ ] Create `/www/cgi-bin/quecmanager/at_cmd/neighbour_scan_start.sh`
  - Endpoint to trigger the scanner worker in the background.
  - Enforces singleton mechanism.
- [ ] Create `/www/cgi-bin/quecmanager/at_cmd/neighbour_scan_status.sh`
  - Endpoint to check scan status (`idle`, `running`, `complete`, [error](file:///d:/Projects/QM%20PROJECT/QManager/scripts/usr/bin/qmanager_cell_scanner#23-24)).
  - Reads `/tmp/qmanager_neighbour_scan_result.json` when complete.

## Phase 2: Frontend Implementation
- [ ] Create `hooks/use-neighbour-scanner.ts`
  - Similar pattern to existing polling hooks (e.g., speedtest).
  - Handles `startScan`, `status` polling (every 1s), and `results` compilation.
- [ ] Update [components/cellular/cell-scanner/neighbourcell/neighbour-scanner.tsx](file:///d:/Projects/QM%20PROJECT/QManager/components/cellular/cell-scanner/neighbourcell/neighbour-scanner.tsx)
  - Remove mock data `mockNeighbourResults`.
  - Connect to `useNeighbourScanner` hook.
  - Implement "Start New Scan" button functionality with loading states.
  - Fix/Implement CSV download functionality using standard frontend download logic.
  - Add visual skeleton loaders while scanning to match UI expectations.

## Phase 3: Verification
- [ ] Manually test LTE neighbour scanning.
- [ ] Manually test NR 5G neighbour scanning.
- [ ] Verify CSV download output format.
- [ ] Verify visual feedback and UI state transitions (loading -> results).
